Comments:	Steps:
		0. Config initialization, open a terminal and run
			$ sudo su
			# cd /usr/local/etc/raddb/certs
			# ./bootstrap
			(get a coffee, when finished modify the user db)
				
		1. Put /usr/local/etc/raddb or other RADDBDIR to your backup
		
		2. Start with: 'sudo /usr/local/etc/init.d/freeradius start'
		   (export env var RADDBDIR= for another directory)
		   
		For a personal database backend install freeradius-sql.tcz
		which supports: unixODBC, mysql, postgresql, sqlite3.
	   	--- 
		This extension is PPI compatible.
